# Next.js Conventions

## Version & Config
- Next.js 16 with App Router — no pages/ directory
- Turbopack for dev server (`next dev --turbopack`)
- Tailwind CSS v4 (imported via `@import "tailwindcss"` in `globals.css`)

## API Routes
- All in `src/app/api/*/route.ts` using route handlers (`POST`, `GET`)
- Server-side only — never expose `FAL_KEY` to the client
- Always return `NextResponse.json(...)` with appropriate status codes
- Handle errors with try/catch and return `{ error: message }` with 500 status

## Client Components
- Mark with `"use client"` at the top when using hooks or browser APIs
- `localStorage` access must be guarded — only in `useEffect` or event handlers
- Use `useState` for workflow step management (`WorkflowStep` type in `types.ts`)

## Styling
- Tailwind utility classes only — no CSS modules
- J.Crew-inspired palette: stone/slate backgrounds, black text, minimal accents
- Custom CSS vars defined in `globals.css` for font families

## No Database
- All approved product data stored in `localStorage` via `src/lib/storage.ts`
- Key: `"jcrew-video-products"` — stores `Product[]` as JSON
